(Sample photos as shown) 

Uncover the beauty of luxury living at its height. Luxurious way of living in a spacious duplex home, high above ground, surrounded by lush gardens of green and a backdrop of blue sky. 

This 32 storey development, 
comprising of 56 apartments, 
will take your breath away every day with a stunning panoramic view of the surrounding city-view. 
A spacious sky terrace, a glass passenger lift, 
a 40-metre swimming pool and a cigar terrace are fine touches to your abode, 
which has a ceiling height of six-metres. 

Vertical living in Singapore can’t get more exciting than this. SkyPark was innovatively conceptualized to turn what would have been constraints being the inherent problems posed by a small plot of high density land in the city into an intelligent multi-layered architectural response. ... 

The intention was to design houses in a residential tower. Experiencing the 'gardens' from within the apartment, the space does actually create a "grounded" sensation, if not for the city skyline beyond. The jury was very impressed by the way in which the architect was able to integrate these design strategies successfully to create meaningful spaces within a coherent piece of architecture. 

Facilities,

Function room 
24hrs security

Fully furnished can be arranged.
Available 23rd Oct 23
(Sample photos as shown) 

Uncover the beauty of luxury living at its height. Luxurious way of living in a spacious duplex home, high above ground, surrounded by lush gardens of green and a backdrop of blue sky. 

This 32 storey development, 
comprising of 56 apartments, 
will take your breath away every day with a stunning panoramic view of the surrounding city-view. 
A spacious sky terrace, a glass passenger lift, 
a 40-metre swimming pool and a cigar terrace are fine touches to your abode, 
which has a ceiling height of six-metres. 

Vertical living in Singapore can’t get more exciting than this. SkyPark was innovatively conceptualized to turn what would have been constraints being the inherent problems posed by a small plot of high density land in the city into an intelligent multi-layered architectural response. ... 

The intention was to design houses in a residential tower. Experiencing the 'gardens' from within the apartment, the space does actually create a "grounded" sensation, if not for the city skyline beyond. The jury was very impressed by the way in which the architect was able to integrate these design strategies successfully to create meaningful spaces within a coherent piece of architecture.

Gym

Function room 
24hrs security

Title: Cozy Master Bedroom at Boon Lay
Location: THE CENTRIS 75 JURONG WEST CENTRAL 3Boon Lay, West Singapore
Description:
'We have a master bedroom, comes with ensuite bathtub, over looking the greenery, serene view.
- Above Boonlay MRT,
- Great facilities, massive pools, reflexology pool, water slide, tennis courts, basketball court, gym, BBQ areas, table tennis etc
- Includes utilities (quarterly aircon servicing, highest speed wifi, washing machine /dryer etc, cooking). 
- Includes weekly cleaning of the common areas and ensuite bathroom
We want you to live here, not just run into your room and hide. Co-living environment
The apartment looks out over gardens and partial pool view. It's rather bright, quiet and gets a nice breeze through the glass window as you rest yourself at the baywindow. There is a dry kitchen/wet kitchen setup with ample room for storage and cooking. An allocated shoerack for your use. There's also a small yard area inside. 
Fully furnished with TV,  King sized bed, huge wardrobe, cabinets and lots of storage.
Kitchen appliances include microwave, oven, 3 tiers steamer, toaster, pressure cooker, air fryer and a Nespresso coffee machine. 
Iron and iron board. Google home in the hall and motion detection lightings.
It is an integrated development situated above Jurong Point Shopping Centre (and Boon Lay MRT). Full facilities, multiple pools, sauna,  water play, tennis courts, BBQs, gym etc. There are all the modern conveniences such as 24hr supermarkets, eateries, abundant shops, several foodcourts catering to all cuisines - Vegetarian, western, local asian, halal etc. Almost 500 shops.
Attached are several childcare centres, education/enrichment centres, banks, clinics, community centre, library, cafes etc.

Available 23rd Oct 23
(Sample photos as shown) 

Uncover the beauty of luxury living at its height. Luxurious way of living in a spacious duplex home, high above ground, surrounded by lush gardens of green and a backdrop of blue sky. 

This 32 storey development, 
comprising of 56 apartments, 
will take your breath away every day with a stunning panoramic view of the surrounding city-view. 
A spacious sky terrace, a glass passenger lift, 
a 40-metre swimming pool and a cigar terrace are fine touches to your abode, 
which has a ceiling height of six-metres. 

Vertical living in Singapore can’t get more exciting than this. SkyPark was innovatively conceptualized to turn what would have been constraints being the inherent problems posed by a small plot of high density land in the city into an intelligent multi-layered architectural response. ... 

The intention was to design houses in a residential tower. Experiencing the 'gardens' from within the apartment, the space does actually create a "grounded" sensation, if not for the city skyline beyond. The jury was very impressed by the way in which the architect was able to integrate these design strategies successfully to create meaningful spaces within a coherent piece of architecture.

Function room 
24hrs security

'Rare Opportunity to Become a Founding Member of a LEGENDARY HOUSE!

Hello, we’re C&K, and we’ve found a gem! We’re looking for intrepid people to come aboard our ENORMOUS semi-detached located in Beauty World.

Creatives welcome! Creators desired! Cat lovers a must! 5 Bedrooms and 4,000 sq ft!

Perks: Mansion Living on a Single Room Budget + Cavernous Interior + SPAAAAAACE + 6 Min Walk to the Blue Line (Beauty World) + 24H Supper Spots for days + A Tabula Rasa: An opportunity to decorate your own space

Cons:  Vintage looks and 60’s Decor- It’s a timewarp! +

Really big, so you’ll need to bring some furniture or invest in your own + 2 Shared Bathrooms: Only one room is equipped with an En-Suite, so some people will have to share! + A Tabula Rasa, so still completely empty! Will need some effort to decorate and furnish. + Not for people with allergies as we have cats

There is a massive outdoor area which we are planning to turn into an urban farm. There will also be kittens around so animal lovers a must!

We have dining tables, a fridge and washing machine and some furniture, but you’ll need to furnish your own room!

We love to socialise so plenty of movie nights, barbeques and board games will be happening! We’re ultimately looking to build a community and home, not to fill a room- Looking for like-minded souls to join us!

En Suite Room - $1800 Available! Inside Room - $1400 Available! XXL Room - $1600 Available! Quiet Room - $1400 Available!'

Vertical living in Singapore can’t get more exciting than this. SkyPark was innovatively conceptualized to turn what would have been constraints being the inherent problems posed by a small plot of high density land in the city into an intelligent multi-layered architectural response. ... 

The intention was to design houses in a residential tower. Experiencing the 'gardens' from within the apartment, the space does actually create a "grounded" sensation, if not for the city skyline beyond. The jury was very impressed by the way in which the architect was able to integrate these design strategies successfully to create meaningful spaces within a coherent piece of architecture. 

Facilities, 
40m Lap pool 
Gym 
BBQ area 
Function room 
24hrs security 
Golf bag storage '

Uncover the beauty of luxury living at its height. Luxurious way of living in a spacious duplex home, high above ground, surrounded by lush gardens of green and a backdrop of blue sky. 

This 32 storey development, 
comprising of 56 apartments,

A spacious sky terrace, a glass passenger lift, 
a 40-metre swimming pool and a cigar terrace are fine touches to your abode, 
which has a ceiling height of six-metres. 

Vertical living in Singapore can’t get more exciting than this. SkyPark was innovatively conceptualized to turn what would have been constraints being the inherent problems posed by a small plot of high density land in the city into an intelligent multi-layered architectural response. ... 

The intention was to design houses in a residential tower. Experiencing the 'gardens' from within the apartment, the space does actually create a "grounded" sensation, if not for the city skyline beyond. Description:
'I'm a Professional Consultant with a cool Designer 5-Room Apartment over
at BLOCK 221, Ang Mo Kio Ave 1, High Floor, bright and breezy. 

I've a B&B HOMESTAY- Deluxe Bedroom for Rent.

GREAT VALUE for the PRICE as a Professional Homestay.
NO AGENT FEES, BREAKFAST, WIFI, UTILITIES INCLUSIVE !!

ROOM AVAILABLE FROM:    7th JAN 2024 !

If you are looking for a Beautiful Home To Live In... THIS IS IT !!
Working Professionals / Internship Students/ PhD Research Fellows Preferred.

Bedroom Furnished with:
1) KING SIZE BED with 12 inch thick SEALY Posturepedic Mattress and 4 Pillows,
2) Built-in 8-Door Wardrobe, 2 locked drawers, plus Extra Storage Overhead,.
3) Writing table with 24in LED Monitor +HDMI input, lamp, High-back chair,
4)Bookshelf, Aircon & Fan,
5)High-Speed 1Gbps Fibre Broadband-LAN/WiFi,
just plug the HDMI to your laptop and stream online content, movies to the big-screen,
6)Electrical Multi-Pin Adapter with USB,
7)Full-Length Mirror
8)Bed Linen, Blankets, 
9) Bath Towels, Bath Essentials, Hair-Dryer. (You Don't Need To Fill Your Luggage 
With These Bulky Items !)

The room doesn't have an en-suite, but a nice clean and bright Bathroom with WET and DRY Areas, please use it accordingly. 

DIY BREAKFAST - Cereal, Bread, Butter, Ham, Cheese, Jam, Milk, Tea and Coffee provided.

You'll have use of the:
1) Washing Machine(Detergent & Fabric Conditioner provided)
2) Clothes Dryer,
3) Steam Iron & Ironing Board,
4) Microwave Oven (light cooking only),
5) Dining Table,
6) Living Room...you don't have to be cooped up in the bedroom all day,
this is a Homestay after all... but keep it tidy please.

I'm on a High floor, nice and breezy with an unblocked view.
Quiet surroundings opposite Bishan Park with a jogging track and outdoor fitness equipment that is just across the road. 
Two 24-Hour Gyms nearby, and an Active Sg Gym just at the next building.

Lots of good local food shops nearby, Fresh-market, two 24-hrs Supermarkets, Bakery, GP Clinic, professional dry-cleaners, 24hr coin-operated laundry shop, Bank ATM's, Hawker Food center, you'll never go hungry living here .... lol
There is a public swimming pool just a short walk down the road, and the central nature reserve is a 15 minute walk away.

My Home is located at the middle of the island, so getting to most places takes just about half an hour.
Just 10 minutes by Feeder Bus number 262 to the
(RED-Line) NS-16, AMK-MRT Station and
Bus numbers 71, 13 & 88 to the (YELLOW CIRCLE-Line) NS-17, BISHAN-MRT Station, 
which is just 8 train stops to NUS University, Kent Ridge MRT Station. (about 16 minutes)

On a fine sunny day, most of my Guests would just walk there in 15 mins+.
The MRT trip from AMK to Raffles Place MRT station takes just 18 minutes.

It takes just 25 mins to the airport and about 10 mins to downtown Orchard Road by cab. There are direct bus services to many areas from here too .

My home environment is suitable for, Considerate, Open-minded Male Professional Interns,  or Working Professional Adults .
L.G.B.T. - Friendly Host .
I would prefer someone like-minded, reasonably tidy, responsible in picking up after themselves and who speaks English as a flatmate.
No smoking in the apartment please.
Cheers, Jeff'

Title: BIG! Spacious Room overlooks Greeneries!
Location: 25 leonie Hill Leonie Gardens Singapore 239225Orchard, Central Singapore
Description:
'A rare find that doesn’t come up in years. Huge gigantic common room that many master rooms can’t even compare to .... in size ! 

Situated at the highest point in Leonie Hill, the prestigious street that’s just off Orchard Road (Somerset / Orchard MRT) and River Valley Road (Great World MRT). Various mode of transport just at door step to almost any parts of Singapore via MRTs and public commute. 

Yet it is just a stone throw to the hub of activities in Orchard Road like Takashimaya/Ion/Wisma Atria/Paragon/Apple Store/Youth Hub/313 Somerset/Orchard Central where the 24 hours japanese supermarket Don Don Donki is located. Food galore from restaurants to food courts that suit all palettes and wallets . Great world city is also another huge mall that’s off River Valley and accessible too. The Great World MRT is just down the slope. 

The condo , Leonie Gardens, comes with a state of the art gymnasium, 2 swimming pools, 4 BBQ pits, yoga/pilates room, tennis/squash/ping pong court & basketball courts. 

The apartment is shared with other likeminded single expats with awesome vibes from all Over the world...and yet every room is quietly separated overlooking immense greeneries. 

Such a tranquil environment that is a rarity and a gem to be found in the heart of Orchard Road . 

The rooms Form part of a 2540 sq ft apartment which explains why they are spectacularly spacious. 

Feel free to message or WhatsApp Michael +65 93255000 or Ellis +65 97905000.

Cheers '
